    "updated_at": "2023-05-18T09:24:48Z",
    "body": "The installer only attempts to use `sudo` if the target binary directory is not writable by the current user. If you use a directory that is writable by your user, you should be able to install starship without `sudo`, for instance: `curl -sS https://starship.rs/install.sh | sh -s -- -b ~/.local/bin`",
